text:
Perpetual long queue at all times.
Friendly & Reasonable price (large generous servings!)

Piping hot dishes from kitchen almost all ready by 1030am.
Good place for Nasi Lemak, Nasi campur or mee siam and Mee Rebus. Always have to queue regardless of weekday or weekend.
I can never get enough of the Mee Rebus from this stall. The peanut sauce is so perfect and very delicious. Always fuel my breakfast. Must try for Mee Rebus lover.
Very nice Malay, the Nasi Sambal Goreng is very delicious and other food also nice

Great variety of Malay dishes! Super delicious! 😋 Authentic old-school dishes like "sayur lemak turi keledek", "paru lembu sambal belado", which are hard to find & come by unless you visit those "ulu kampong warongs" in Malaysia. The "sambal belachan" is super fiery! Proceed with caution! 😝😜🤪

They have beef bakso noodles, the usual culprits like lontong, mee siam, mee soto, soto ayam, mee rebus etc.

Of course, you should try the mee soto with extra bergedil. 😋😋😋

Y'all must try it, yo!
